    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.35-36_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">36</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">BOSTON COLLEGE
                        <lb/>
                    CHESTNUT HILL
                        <lb/>
                    MASSACHUSETTS</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Oct. 17.</dateline>
                
                    Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I received a copy of your review of my book of verses: Boundaries. This is the second time you have reviewed me, and each time with a sweetness (there ought to be some occasion when this word may be used since we have no "douceur" like the French) that makes me <unclear>your debtor</unclear>.</p>
                
                <p>I have known you as a poet for a long time. Indeed you were first recommended to me by a Catholic nun. So please accept my thanks both for your criticisms and for your poetry.</p>
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>Leonard Feeney <unclear>J.</unclear></signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.35-36_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">246 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">35</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <note type="unknown"><unclear><hi rend="caps">L. F.</hi></unclear></note>         
                    <hi rend="caps">BOSTON COLLEGE
                        <lb/>
                    UNIVERSITY HEIGHTS
                        <lb/>
                    CHESTNUT HILL, MASS.</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <note type="recipient">Father Leonard
                Feeney,</note>

                <ab type="postmark">
                    BOSTON, MASS. W
                    OCT 17
                    930PM
                    1935
                    
                    BUY U.S. SAVINGS
                    BONDS
                    ASK YOUR POSTMASTER
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POSTAGE WASHINGTON 3 CENTS 3</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>c/o The Saint Louis Post-Dispatch</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><del>Saint Louis</del></addrLine>
                        <addrLine><add>Branson,</add> Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
